The Run App API in 23.07 will be called like this.

```run_app_payload = {
        'input_dir': input_file_dir,
        'name': app_name,
    }
    run_app_resp = requests.post (http://requests.post)(f'{API_BASE_URL}/v2/projects/app/run', headers=API_HEADERS, data=run_app_payload)
    if run_app_resp.status_code != 202:
        raise RuntimeError(f'App Run API failed: {run_app_resp.status_code} {run_app_resp.text}')```
The main thing to note is that the only thing a user has to configure now is the input directory and the App Name. There are no more long hard-to-understand unique idâ€™s.
